        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 4:47PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Uptown Charlotte, or near Paw Creek, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwest Charlotte, Freedom Park, The Plaza, Charlotte Douglas
Airport, Belmont, Central Charlotte, Uptown Charlotte, Mt Holly,
Croft, and Northeast Charlotte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
